In that case you want the ARM64 .deb, not the amd64 one.
âœ… Correct download URL for Heartbeat 8.12.0 on ARM Ubuntu
wget https://artifacts.elastic.co/downloads/beats/heartbeat/heartbeat-8.12.0-arm64.deb
Install it
sudo dpkg -i heartbeat-8.12.0-arm64.deb
If you hit dependency issues (common on fresh installs):
sudo apt-get -f install
Verify architecture (optional but reassuring)
uname -m
You should see:
aarch64

Where things end up
Config: /etc/heartbeat/heartbeat.yml
Service: heartbeat
Logs: /var/log/heartbeat/
Start it:

sudo systemctl start heartbeat
sudo systemctl status heartbeat

if the above command give you an error. Run it through the binaries

3ï¸âƒ£ Check if the service file exists
Heartbeat should install this file:
/lib/systemd/system/heartbeat.service
Check:
ls -l /lib/systemd/system | grep heartbeat
If it exists, reload systemd:
sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
Then start it:
sudo systemctl start heartbeat
4ï¸âƒ£ Check if Heartbeat binary exists at all
which heartbeat
or:
ls /usr/share/heartbeat/
If Heartbeat is missing, the .deb did not install correctly.
5ï¸âƒ£ Quick sanity test (run manually)
Even without systemd, you can test it:
heartbeat version
or:
sudo /usr/share/heartbeat/heartbeat test config
If this works, weâ€™re very close.
TL;DR (fastest path)
Run these in order:
dpkg -l | grep heartbeat
sudo dpkg -i heartbeat-8.12.0-arm64.deb
sudo apt-get -f install
dpkg -l | grep heartbeat
ls /lib/systemd/system/heartbeat.service

